@FlandreScarlet Thanks!

@elmindreda I'm sorry, the title is summarized. In the example:
```c
void joystick_callback(int joy, int event)
{
    if (event == GLFW_CONNECTED)
    {
        // The joystick was connected
    }
    else if (event == GLFW_DISCONNECTED)
    {
        // The joystick was disconnected
    }
}
```
The "event" that I was referring to.
Sorry if it's not an issue but as the GLFW_CONNECTED occurs, I was expecting the GLFW_DISCONNECTED without code about joystick in main loop yet, like a callback behavior. Is it possible?
